n_4093435\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hmg1665702909230_2.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hmg1665702909230_2.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hmg1665702909230_2.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hmg1665702909230\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Data Copy Facilities and Referential Integrity\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"hmg1665702909230__data_copy_facilities_and_referential_integrity_141824\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Referential integrity can be temporarily violated while loading large amounts of data in related entities. Uniface provides utilities that allow large-scale loading of data into Uniface;\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hmg1665702909230__p_d46994e1_d46995e1_d46996e1\">Uniface provides the Data Copy facility for loading data into databases. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wxi1665702696586.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wxi1665702696586.html\" title=\"Uniface enables you to copy and convert your application data to and from different formats, including XML files and other databases.\">Data Copy Facility</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hmg1665702909230__p_d47000e1_d47001e1_d47002e1\">Referential integrity can be temporarily violated if one or more occurrences of a Many entity in a relationship is loaded before the related occurrence of the one entity has been loaded. The violation ceases as soon as the related occurrence of the one entity is also loaded.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hmg1665702909230__p_d47003e1_d47004e1_d47005e1\">Uniface regularly commits at short intervals during large load operations (unless disabled with a connector option), because many DBMSs impose restrictions on the size of transactions. This can result in related occurrences being stored in separate transactions, which temporarily violates referential integrity. If a commit occurs in a DBMS, that is, referential integrity has been violated, the DBMS will rollback the transaction.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hmg1665702909230__p_d47006e1_d47007e1_d47008e1\">For this reason, you need to temporarily disable the DBMS enforced referential integrity when performing a batch load operation.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4093435\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4093435\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Data Copy Facilities and Referential Integrity Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Data Copy Facilities and Referential Integrity Referential integrity can be temporarily violated while loading large amounts of data in related entities. Uniface provides utilities that allow large-scale loading of data into Uniface; Uniface provides the Data Copy facility for loading data into databases. For more information, see Data Copy Facility . Referential integrity can be temporarily violated if one or more occurrences of a Many entity in a relationship is loaded before the related occurrence of the one entity has been loaded. The violation ceases as soon as the related occurrence of the one entity is also loaded. Uniface regularly commits at short intervals during large load operations (unless disabled with a connector option), because many DBMSs impose restrictions on the size of transactions. This can result in related occurrences being stored in separate transactions, which temporarily violates referential integrity. If a commit occurs in a DBMS, that is, referential integrity has been violated, the DBMS will rollback the transaction. For this reason, you need to temporarily disable the DBMS enforced referential integrity when performing a batch load operation. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}